channel.title: Team Walrus - BM fans invade TF2 to the dismay of many
channel.description:
Just giving a shout out to Keresh, SassyRobot, Spooks, AngryMonkE and anyone I've forgotten for the great fun it was playing TF2 with you all. Since my clan has moved onto L4D more these days it's been too long since I've had that much fun playing TF2, and we should do it again, often. :slight_smile:
Like tonight for example? And every weekend henceforth? I could try and get my clan together as well, we could fill a server with hilarity and good times. And any other European Bm fans should look us up if you fancy a game too, I'll be in the BM chat room as often as possible so folks can find us.
Oh, and because I thought it might amuse you, I copied my friend and clan-mate Reb's reaction to joining the server where Team Walrus was spinning right round:
[COLOR='Green'][-TSG-] Reb: who the hell are these people O_O [COLOR='DarkRed'][-TSG-] raw_bean: haha [-TSG-] raw_bean: peeps from the Black Mesa mod forums [-TSG-] raw_bean: where I moderate [COLOR='Green'][-TSG-] Reb: ah [-TSG-] Reb: They are still mad.... [-TSG-] Reb: Im going to hate walrus's after this [-TSG-] Reb: Besides mad who the hell is that Sanfrod person lol [COLOR='DarkRed'][-TSG-] raw_bean: lol She's a really cool lass from Oxford, called Rebecca (hence the Reb confusion). Her boyfriend's pretty cool too, though slightly less mad and not on the server tonight [COLOR='Green'][-TSG-] Reb: Ah right O_O [-TSG-] Reb: I was slightly confused whether it was a really young lad or a girl. its hard to tell sometimes [COLOR='DarkRed'][-TSG-] raw_bean: lol, I know what you mean [-TSG-] raw_bean: but if you'd seen what she said in team chat you'd have probably guessed: "I don't know why I'm not more popular. Girl gamer, big boobs, surely I check all the boxes" [-TSG-] raw_bean: I told her it worked fopr me lol [COLOR='Green'][-TSG-] Reb: lamo

Acristoff:

So where is the north america team walrus?

Start your own team. Ours started as a group of regulars who met in the BM chat room and started playing TF2 together a lot. You could try and do something similar, or create a thread here looking for American TF2 players among the BM fans and trying to arrange some games.

Justice:

May I request an invite to the team of spinning walruses?

Keep dropping in on the BM chat room in the Steam community to meet us, and you’ll get the chance to play TF2 with us on some evening. Then we’ll see about inviting you in.
